    "body": "AI content generation Storyraise has AI built in to help with the hardest part of any report: the blank page. Use it to draft whole sections and to generate imagery — then make the results your own. Draft a section with AI The Describe & Draft a New Section tool builds entire report sections from a description: Click Add new section and choose the AI drafting option. Describe what the section is about — for example, \"Our youth mentorship program matched 120 students with mentors this year, with 94% reporting improved confidence.\" Or pick one of the suggested ideas to start. Click generate. Storyraise outlines and drafts the section for you. Edit the result like any other section — adjust the words, swap images, restyle. Getting good drafts Give it your numbers and names. \"We served 3,400 meals at our downtown shelter\" produces a far better draft than \"write about our food program.\" One section per ask. Describe a single topic; build the report section by section. Treat it as a first draft. The AI gets you from blank to rough; your voice and your details make it real. Always review before publishing. Generate images with AI Where you add media, you can also generate it: describe the image you want and Storyraise creates it. Useful for illustrative and decorative imagery when you don't have a photo that fits. A word of advice: for impact storytelling, real photos of your real work will always beat generated images. Use AI imagery for abstract or decorative spots, not in place…"
