    "body": "Reordering sections The order of your sections is the arc of your story. Storyraise makes it easy to rearrange sections as your report takes shape. Reorder by drag and drop Open the section sorter — the view that shows all your sections as a list with drag handles. Drag a section by its handle to its new position. The report's reading order and navigation menu update to match. Order changes everything else Reordering updates the report's table of contents , which drives the reader-facing navigation menu — there's nothing to fix up manually after a move. See Navigation options . Thinking about order A structure that works for most impact reports: Hook — an Intro block with your strongest image and a clear theme Credibility — a Letter from leadership Proof — Stories, Stats, and Galleries, alternating narrative and visual blocks Gratitude — Testimonials and your Donor List Ask — a Donate block while the impact is fresh Two practical tips: Put your best story early. Many readers won't reach the end; don't save the strongest material for last. End with the ask. The Donate section belongs after the emotional peak, not before it."
