    "body": "Understanding report metrics Once your report is published and shared, Insights shows you how it's performing. From the dashboard, open a published report's menu and choose View Insights . This page walks through every metric you'll see. Two views: The Numbers and The Story Insights has two tabs: The Numbers — every metric, chart, and list, for when you want the detail. The Story — an AI-written narrative summary of your report's performance, ready to read aloud in a staff meeting or export as a PDF for your board. The headline metrics Opens — total times your report has been viewed. Return visits count, so a report people come back to earns its number. Constituents Reached — how many known constituents opened the report. This counts people identified through their personalized links ; anonymous visits don't appear here. Avg. Time Spent — how long visitors stay per visit. A strong signal of whether the report holds attention. Avg. Sections Viewed — how far into the report visitors get on average. Avg. Time per Section — how long readers spend on each section they reach. Reading them together The combinations matter more than any single number: High Opens, low time spent — your distribution worked but the opening sections aren't holding people. Strengthen the first two sections. High time spent, few sections viewed — readers are absorbed early but not progressing. Check whether a long early section needs splitting. Opens far above Constituents Reached — most visits are…"
