    "body": "Setting up your account Getting started on Storyraise takes a couple of minutes. This guide walks you from the sign-up screen to your new dashboard. Create your account Go to the sign-up page and fill in Create your Storyraise account : Organization Name — your nonprofit's name, e.g. The SR Foundation . Storyraise URL — the web address your published reports will live under. Storyraise suggests one based on your organization name (like sr.storyraise.com ), and you can edit it. This becomes your reports' home: https://your-organization.yearly.report . Full Name — your name. Title — your role (optional). Work Email — the address you'll sign in with. Create a Password — use the show/hide toggle to check it. Agree to the Terms & Conditions and create your account. Prefer Google? Use Sign up with Google to skip the password step. Confirm your URL After the first step, you'll get one last chance to fine-tune your Storyraise URL — Awesome! One last thing. Choose carefully: this subdomain appears in every report link you share, so pick something short and recognizable (your organization's name or acronym works well). What happens next You land on your dashboard, ready to build. A strong first hour: Set up your brand kit — add your logo, colors, and fonts so every report starts on brand. See Brand kit . Create your first report — start from a template. See Creating your first report . Invite your team — bring colleagues into your organization. See Managing your team . Import your…"
