    "body": "Organization settings Your organization is the shared workspace that holds your reports, constituents, brand kit, and team. This page covers the organization-level settings in your account area. Your organization info Under Your Org Info you'll find: Organization Name — how your organization is identified across Storyraise. Custom URL — your reports' web address, your-organization.yearly.report . These are shown for reference. To change them, contact support — your URL in particular is woven into every published report link, so it isn't edited casually. Your brand Most of what makes your organization look like your organization lives in the brand kit — logos, colors, and primary/secondary fonts that apply across every report. See Brand kit . Nonprofit certificate Organization admins can upload your nonprofit certificate under Nonprofit Certificate ( Add docs — PDF or DOC). This verifies your nonprofit status with Storyraise. Upload it once; you can replace or remove it later. Sending email from your domain To send email from your own domain (so messages come from you@yourdomain.org rather than a Storyraise address), set up a custom sending domain. See Setting up a custom sending domain . Belonging to more than one organization If you work with multiple organizations on Storyraise — say, a foundation and a fiscally sponsored project — you can belong to several at once. Use Find account to search your organizations and switch between them; each has its own reports,…"
