    "body": "Your profile and security This page covers your personal account — your name and sign-in details — and how to secure it with two-step verification. Your info Under Your Info you can see your name and email and make changes: Update email — change the address you sign in with. Update password — set a new password. Resetting a forgotten password If you can't sign in, use the password-reset option. Storyraise emails you reset instructions — \"Check your email at [your address]. We've sent password reset instructions.\" Follow the link in that email to set a new password. Verify your email Before you can turn on two-step verification, your email address must be verified. If it isn't yet, Storyraise will prompt you and send a verification link — \"You must verify your email before enabling multi-factor authentication.\" Click the link in that email, then return to your settings. Two-step verification (MFA) Two-step verification adds a second check at sign-in, so a stolen password alone can't get into your account. Storyraise supports two methods, set up on the Two-step verification page: Authenticator app (recommended) Choose Add authenticator app . Scan the QR code with an authenticator app (Google Authenticator, Authy, 1Password, etc.). Enter the 6-digit code the app shows to confirm. Optionally give it a display name. Authenticator apps work even without cell signal, which makes them more reliable than SMS. Text message (SMS) In Multi-factor Authentication (MFA) , enter your…"
